<li id="cite_note-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Nauvoo_Expositor"><i>Nauvoo Expositor</i></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Nauvoo+Expositor&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikisource.org%2Fwiki%2FNauvoo_Expositor&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-historyOfLDS-council-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-historyOfLDS-council_15-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=pGi-iiz6juYC&amp;pg=PA430&amp;lpg=PA432"><i>History of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</i></a> volume VI (1912), pp. 430-432. The council met on June 8 and June 10 to discuss the matter.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-historyOfLDS-destructionOrder-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-historyOfLDS-destructionOrder_16-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=pGi-iiz6juYC&amp;pg=PA432&amp;lpg=PA432"><i>History of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</i></a> volume VI (1912), p. 432: "The Council passed an ordinance declaring the <i>Nauvoo Expositor</i> a nuisance, and also issued an order to me to abate the said nuisance. I immediately ordered the Marshall to destroy it without delay." – Joseph Smith</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Encyclopedia of Latter-Day Saint History pg. 824.</span>
</li>
